   [] [15blank.gif]
   Obligor: Community Home Health & Hospice is a home health and hospice
   care facility located in Longview, WA.
   Loan Size: $1,283,000
   Description of Loan: The loan is to refinance an existing taxable loan
   originally borrowed to acquire their existing facility and for upgraded
   computer software.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $180,000 over the life of the bond
   issue.
   Underwriter: Quick Loan with Cowlitz Bank, Longview, WA.
   Closing Date: October 22, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: Family Health Centers operates three medical clinics located
   in Tonasket, Okanogan and Brewster and two dental clinics located in
   Okanogan and Pateros.
   Loan Size: $825,000
   Description of Loan: This loan is to refinance two existing taxable
   loans originally borrowed to construct and remodel two medical clinics
   and the acquisition of a dental clinic.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $650,000 over the life of the bond
   issue.
   Underwriter: Quick Loan with Washington Trust Bank, Spokane, WA.
   Closing Date: November 13, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: Childrens Hospital & Regional Medical Center is a regional
   pediatric center that offers a full range of inpatient and outpatient
   diagnostic and therapeutic services and related ancillary services. The
   Hospital is affiliated with the University of Washington School of
   Medicine and is the primary practice site for the pediatric faculty of
   the school.
   Loan Size: $80,000,000
   Description of Loan: The loan will provide a portion of the funding for
   a $120 million capital program to construct a new parking garage, a new
   inpatient facility and administrative building as well as the
   acquisition of major medical and other equipment.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $30,000,000 over the life of the
   bond issue (30 years).
   Underwriter: UBS PaineWebber, Inc.
   Closing Date: December 5, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: The Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center is a Washington
   nonprofit corporation with a mission to eliminate cancer as a cause of
   human suffering and death.
   Loan Size: $138,700,000
   Description of Loan: This proposed financing is for Phase IV of the
   Centers overall plan to consolidate all of its operations at the Robert
   W. Day Campus at South Lake Union. Phase IV includes the purchase of
   land and construction and equipping an office building to house the
   Public Health Sciences Division of the Center.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $75,000,000 over the life of the
   bond issue.
   Underwriter: Lehman Brothers
   Closing Date: November 15, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: Kadlec Medical Center, located in Richland, WA, provides
   general inpatient services. In addition, Cardiac Surgery and associated
   cardiac support services began August 2001.
   Loan Size: $9,747,035
   Description of Loan: The loan is for Diagnostic Imaging equipment and
   accessories. The large purchases will be X-Ray equipment, Mammography
   equipment, CT Scanner, CT/Pet Scanner, MRI, Nuclear Medicine Camera,
   Ultrasound equipment and archiving capacity for all equipment.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $980,000 over the life of the
   lease/purchase.
   Underwriter: Private Placement with G.E. Capital Public Finance, Inc.
   Closing Date: November 9, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: The Inland Northwest Blood Center (INBC) collects, markets,
   processes, and distributes blood and blood components throughout the
   Inland Northwest. It also provides medical support services such as
   organ typing and testing and selected therapeutic patient services.
   INBC is also the donor registration arm for the National Marrow
   Donation Program for eastern
   Loan Size: $8,990,000
   Description of Loan: The loan proceeds will be used to construct and
   equip a new replacement facility for INBC in Spokane, WA.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $5,000,000 over the life of the
   bond issue (25 years)
   Underwriter: Banc of America Securities LLC
   Closing Date: August 16, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: Good Samaritan Community Healthcare, located in Puyallup, WA,
   is a non-profit, community based, comprehensive health care delivery
   system serving residents of Pierce and South King Counties.
   Loan Size: $50,000,000
   Description of Loan: The first phase of a two phase project consists of
   a new west wing to house the Family Birth Center and new space for the
   existing Health Rehabilitation Center; expansion of the emergency
   department; remodel of the first floor support services area,
   installation of a new cardiac catheterization lab and the purchase of
   various capital equipment. The second phase will cover expansion and/or
   replacement of the existing surgical and ancillary services departments
   and related equipment.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $33,000,000 over the life of the
   bond issue (30 years).
   Underwriter: Merrill Lynch & Co.
   Closing Date: December 12, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: Group Health Cooperative of Puget Sound is a non-profit health
   care system of hospitals and medical centers, an associated 1,050
   physician group practice, the Northwests largest HMO; a research center
   and a charitable foundation.
   Loan Size: $66,215,000
   Description of Loan: Refinancing all of the outstanding Washington
   Health Care Facilities Authority Series 1989 Revenue Bonds.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $4,000,000 per year.
   Underwriter: Salomon Smith Barney
   Closing Date: November 21, 2001

                                 [line1.gif]
   Obligor: PeaceHealth consists of five regional health care delivery
   systems, two of which are St. Joseph Hospital in Bellingham, WA and St.
   John Medical Center in Longview, WA.
   Loan Size: $80,000,000
   Description of Loan: Approximately $57.6 million is for new
   construction at St. Joseph Hospital. Two floors will be added to the
   existing tower of the north campus, one floor is for 34 beds in private
   rooms and the second floor is for future expansion. Two floors will be
   added above the current surgery area of the south campus and will be
   used for surgical and diagnostic services, inpatient mental health
   unit, inpatient rehab and a cardiovascular center. A four-story garage
   will be built as well as a physical plant expansion for back up
   emergency generator and chillers needed due to expansion. Approximately
   $4 million will be used for remodeling of various departments and major
   building systems within St. John Medical Center. The balance is for
   equipment purchases.
   Interest Cost Savings: Estimated at $30,000,000 over the life of the
   bond issue.
   Underwriter: Goldman Sach's
   Closing Date: November 6, 2001

